== 概要 ==
This template facilitates the attribution of articles from either an external source or from the [[s:Easton's Bible Dictionary|Wikisource project]] [[Easton's Bible Dictionary]] in the manner of {{tl|cite encyclopedia}}.

This template should usually be placed on the '''main''' page of the article, in the "References" section near the bottom of the page (see [[:en:WP:Plagiarism#Where to place attribution]]).

== 參數及使用方法 ==
List of parameters
 noicon=''x'' – if set removes the icon from the start of the citation
 prescript=''string'' – alter prescript to ''string'', 
                    for no prescript see {{tlx|Cite EBD}}  
 inline=''x'' — alter the prescript from "This article"
            to "One or more of the preceding sentences"
 short=''x''  — prevents author, publisher and edition information being displayed
 ref=harv — default. can be modified by setting the parameter
            to another value (see {{tlx|cite encyclopedia}})
 encyclopedia=Easton's Bible Dictionary — default setting. Can be modified
 year=1897 — default setting. Can be modified
 last=Easton — default setting. Can be modified
 authorlink=Matthew George Easton  — default setting. Can be modified
 edition=New and revised — default setting. Can be modified
 publisher=T. Nelson and Sons  — default setting. Can be modified
 wstitle=''EBD article name'' — set if the EBD article resides on [[Wikisource]]
 title=''EBD article name''  — set if the EBD article does not reside on Wikisource
 url=''article link''  — set if the EBD article resides on a known external web server
 volume=''volume number'' — not set by default see (see {{tlx|cite encyclopedia}})
 page=''page number''  — not set by default see (see {{tlx|cite encyclopedia}})
 pages=''page number''  — not set by default see (see {{tl|cite encyclopedia}})

To link to an article on Wikisource:
*<code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>EBD|wstitle=''EBD article name''}}</code>
or to name an article and optionally link to another site using the url parameter:
*<code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>EBD|title=''EBD article name''|url=''url here''}}</code>

Using the article name ''[[Samaritan Pentateuch]]'' as an example with wstitle=:
:<code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>EBD|wstitle=Samaritan Pentateuch}}</code>
*{{EBD|wstitle=Samaritan Pentateuch}}
and with title= and url=
:<code><nowiki>{{EBD|title=Samaritan Pentateuch|url=http://archive.org/stream/illustratedbible00east#page/598/mode/1up}}</nowiki></code>
*{{EBD|title=Samaritan Pentateuch|url=http://archive.org/stream/illustratedbible00east#page/598/mode/1up}}

The parameter noicon=''x'' stops the display of the icon:
*{{EBD|wstitle=Samaritan Pentateuch |noicon=x}}

The parameter short=''x'' removes author, publisher and edition information:
*{{EBD|wstitle=Samaritan Pentateuch |short=x}}

Combining noicon=''x'' and short=''x'':
*{{EBD|wstitle=Samaritan Pentateuch |short=1| noicon=1}}

